Nyali&nbsp;MP&nbsp;Hezron&nbsp;Awiti&nbsp;yesterday&nbsp;unveiled&nbsp;his&nbsp;new&nbsp;political&nbsp;party&nbsp;and&nbsp;running&nbsp;mate&nbsp;for the&nbsp;Mombasa&nbsp;gubernatorial&nbsp;race.&nbsp;Mr&nbsp;Awiti,&nbsp;who&nbsp;recently&nbsp;quit&nbsp;the&nbsp;Kalonzo&nbsp;Musyoka-led&nbsp;Wiper&nbsp;Democratic Movement&nbsp;(WDM) will&nbsp;have&nbsp;Hassan&nbsp;Mwamtoa, a&nbsp;banker, as&nbsp;his&nbsp;running&nbsp;mate&nbsp;in the&nbsp;August&nbsp;polls. The&nbsp;two&nbsp;will be&nbsp;running&nbsp;on a&nbsp;Democratic&nbsp;Party&nbsp;ticket&nbsp;where&nbsp;Awiti, a&nbsp;former&nbsp;national&nbsp;treasurer&nbsp;of&nbsp;WDM, is&nbsp;party&nbsp;leader. Mwamtoa, a Digo from Likoni Sub-county in&nbsp;Mombasa, was endorsed by Mijikenda community elders.&nbsp;Awiti&nbsp;announced that the Mijikenda community from which&nbsp;his&nbsp;running&nbsp;mate&nbsp;is drawn, will share the county government on a 50-50 basis with other communities if he wins the seat. &quot;The Mijikenda will share the county government with other communities in the county on a 50-50 basis,&quot;&nbsp;Awitisaid. Other&nbsp;gubernatorial&nbsp;candidates seeking to unseat Governor&nbsp;Hassan&nbsp;Joho are Suleiman Shahbal of Jubilee and&nbsp;Hassan&nbsp;Omar of&nbsp;WDM. The Mijikenda community is seen to be the best&nbsp;political bait for&nbsp;gubernatorial&nbsp;candidates in&nbsp;Mombasa&nbsp;because it forms the biggest voting bloc.&nbsp;